Some days ago I was convinced by my friend Fernando to start learning Java. I wondered, &ldquo;Why not?&rdquo;. While examining the first chapters of Java - A Beginner&rsquo;s Guide, I stumbled upon this interesting &ldquo;issue&rdquo;.
Because of Java&rsquo;s automatic type promotion in expressions, an aparently correct code can cause compilation errors. See&hellip;
byte b = 20; b = b * 2; // This will trigger a compilation error. You can&#39;t assign an int to a byte.
